This paper is about sentiment classification, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP). The use of attention-based encoders and pre-trained BERT models suggests that this paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). Additionally, the use of regularization techniques and analysis of model effectiveness suggests that this paper may also belong to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The task of sentiment classification also involves information retrieval (IR) and neural networks (NE), which are other possible sub-categories.
